article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 85, CS Northridge 70
article.story: NORTHRIDGE, Calif. -- Orlando Johnson scored 25 points and Alan Williams scored 19 and grabbed nine rebounds to help UC Santa Barbara earn an 85-70 victory over Cal State Northridge on Thursday night. James Nunnally scored 14 points and T.J. Taylor had nine assists for UC Santa Barbara (12-7, 7-2 Big West). Cal State Northridge (6-14, 2-7) got 15 points from Josh Greene, 12 from Stephan Hicks and 11 from Vinnie McGhee. Greene connected on four 3-pointers. Stephen Maxwell had eight rebounds. Cal State Northridge had been seeking a split in the two-game season series after UC Santa Barbara won 69-61 on Jan. 19.
